This is where I come to say the things that are not to be heard or seen. Seems most people have forgotten about this site. I'm really quite glad to know it. My thoughts are safe here.... for the most part I guess.

I am laying in my bed; alone. Nothing on but my skivvies! Boy it's nice. Nice to just be. Be warm and cool at the same time. Fan + a summer night = lovely combination..


........



So, I'm here. And I can sense great things getting closer. It's the weeks prior that very nearly drive me mad. Sitting. Waiting. Wishing. Fantasizing about what could happen. It's very love-hate type thing. hA. Funny... when anticipation is running high, nothing ever happens. So, I keep myself stocked up on pot and ciggs. Just a couple of things to pass the time more efficiently... between now and the end of my days really.... huh.



I have very nearly lost my mind waiting to feel your hand in mine. Since the day I was born, I've craved to be turned inside out by your caress. And now, I find I've missed out; wasted my days waiting for the man I had only pictured in my head... and not the one who stood before me so long ago and confessed his love.

- My Inner Old Lady

This relationship sucks. I feel like I have gotten caught up in a vicious cycle. We never do anything fun. I've gained 20 pounds because the only thing available to eat when I come over is fucking cheesburgers. We lay in bed all the time. Waste the day. Get fat. Then we get up and fight, get drunk(sometimes). This is not what I want. He never wants to go do anything. There's never any money to go out and do anything. I cannot understand why I hang around for this. Something, someone. Please give me a push! Give me the balls to end it once and for all!!!! I cannot take this anymore! My health is suffering. My self esteem is suffering. I do not enjoy it anymore!!!!

WHY AM I PUTTING MYSELF THROUGH THIS?????????

i have become socially inactive and i like it. i work, i come home, talk to my boyfriend and relax for the rest of the evening.

today is the start of something new. sort of. i am moving back home with the parents. things are going to be really really tough. i've had more freedom lately than i am used to and now it's all going to be taken away. i can't wait until i have a job. i'll never have to be around to put up with anything. i really wish things had worked out. the tension is getting unbearable. it might just be on my end. i dont know, but i've had about as much as i can stand. once i get back on my meds i think everything will be a lot easier for a while. my mom is making go to counseling. that isn't a bad thing. what's the worst that can come of it? either boredom or i feel a lot better. so that won't be a problem. the main thing keeping me going right now is my boyfriend. he is my motivation. in a few months (well... probably more than a few) if all goes as planned, then i'll be able to see him a lot more, have a new place, be away from nagging parents and i can start building my own life. man... that'll be sweet. 

but first get a job, pay off those hospital bills, insurance and save save save.

also, my mom keeps everything as far as food goes and it pissed my dad off prettty bad. haha. he was going through the refigerator and kept finding bad food and throwing it really hard into the trash can. he said a little something like this:

so many thoughts right now. i suppose i will begin with new years eve. it was amazing to say the least. my friend chase picked me up at home around 11:30 and we headed to winston-salem. we met up with some guys at school and discussed plans. we all decided to go climb the tallest building on campus and hang out on the roof. it was quite an adventure. it wasn't as easy as i thought it was going to be just because of pipes, ledges, ladders, steep rooves, etc. anyway, we got to the top and the view was great. we sat there for a few hours and shared a bottle of champagne. who knows how much later, it was getting pretty cold so we decided to leave. getting down was interesting. never attempt to get off of very tall buildings while intoxicated. BAD IDEA. chase and i drove off to find food. cookout was open, so we ate there. cheese fries. mmm. after that we went to this guys house and crashed. it was a very fun night. i got home today around 1:00 pm looking pretty hoboesque with a 40 oz in hand. my mom was in the kitchen waiting for me. i told her about my adventures and all was well. she left soon after and i finished my supply. adrienne came over and we talked about our evenings and stuff. she left a couple hours later and i went to sleep. that was my night/day. fun fun.


tomorrow i have to go to school and pack all of my stuff at school. i am really sad about leaving. i want to cry everytime i think about it. i hope i am making the right choice. this is a lot harder than i thought it was going to be. so much shit here at home.... i hate it. i'm always being yelled at. always being told that i never put any effort into anything. always being told that i am using my parents... having an attitude, etc. fuck them. i'm not using them. i dont want to. that would make me a worthless shithead and i am definitely not that. not even close. i have til the end of the month to find a job or i have to leave home or join the military. fair enough. military is out of the question. and if i dont get any of the jobs i have applied for, i guess i would be considered homeless. 

my heart feels like it is being pulled and twisted in the most painful way i have ever felt. it's hard to take. it's so hard to get through the day without breaking down because you want something you can't have. i hate this.

so i guess we all have those days when it feels like everyone hates you? maybe? today is one of those days. mos def. i dont get whats wrong with me. i think i am civil to people. maybe even nice. and i am fucking honest as hell. i would give anything for any of my friends. sometimes i just feel like i don't measure up to their level of whatever it is they are. therefore, they stop talking to me, ignore my im's, phonecalls, etc. and when i see them in person and we talk, it feels like they are forcing themselves to put on a happy face and pretend that they like me for whatever reason. it hurts a lot. all i ask for from someone is honesty. that's it. and if you think i'm the most annoying person on the face of the earth, then tell me and we'll leave it at that. i'll never say a word to you again. things would be more simple that way. it's better than wondering.
hey everybody. i hate christmas. but uh... everyone have a good one and stuff. love you all.

i left home sunday morning. i went to megans house. i stayed there last night and was thinking about going home today, but my mind has changed. i called home to talk to my dad and my brother answered. he gave the phone to my mom... exactly what i didn't want. she told me to call back at 9:00. i did and this was our conversation:

me: hi.
mom: hi. we need to talk. 
me: go ahead. 
mom: well, i cant talk to you right now about it. you need to be here at home.
me:  what do you need to talk to me about? 
mom: well, i made you an appointment at 8:30 on wednesday. 
me: an appointment for what? 
mom: an appointment for you to get a pap smear. 
me: what? a pap smear? why...no. do you know what? screw you. i didnt have sex with him. im not a fucking whore. goodbye.

i hung up on her. i called again:

me: oh, and one more thing. i'm not going. goodbye.

so things aren't going so well. i've gotten my heart broken and my mom thinks i'm a slut. she isn't concerned about whether or not i'm carrying diseases. i just went to the obgyn a couple weeks ago, so she knows i'm not. she wants to satisfy her curiosity. fuck that.
1. It's none of her business.
2. She went behind my back.
3. She's being a nosy bitch.
4. It's none of her business.
5. I didn't sleep with him.

i won't be going home for a while. i hate everything right now. i want to leave. my parents don't know where i am and i want it to stay that way. i'll be moving around quite a bit these next few weeks. let  me know if you have an extra room.
